Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners of a race since April 25 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000 (Claiming races for $12,500 or less not considered in estimating allowances). (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SON OF GRACE was taken outside and unhurried early, rallied around the second turn, bid six wide, closed willingly, got up late and inched clear. GATE CREW was in tight at the start, raced mid pack, rallied on the turn, bid four wide to challenge, dueled through the stretch and was outclosed. PINBALLER vied inside to the second turn, inched clear, responded when challenged to duel for the lead, didn't have enough late and settled for show. FORWARD CURVE was well placed, bid inside on the turn, dueled for the lead and came up empty late. COMMAND CENTRAL pressed the pace while racing three across, fell back on the turn and continued willingly to the wire. MEMPHIS PRAYER saved ground, angled out for the drive and offered a mild bid only. UNCLE NICK raced in hand around the first turn, saved ground, bid inside and had nothing left for the drive. BEEASY was slow early, altered course in the upper stretch and lacked a bid. LOOK AWAY trailed the field and passed a tiring rival. POWERFUL MAN vied between horses, tired on the turn and stopped.
